description: Story is reprinted from Justice League of America #21 - Crisis on Earth-One!
name: Crise na Terra Um

volume.name: As You Like It, Charlie Brown

description: The year is 2085. World War IV: The Metahuman War is at its peak. The world's greatest superhero, Centura, returns from a ten year absence and goes to Europe to stop the war. It has been three days and no one has heard from him. It's now up to his former sidekick and a new breed of heroes to discover his fate, and the fate of the world at large.

Science Fiction Noir. For the true cognoscenti of classic sci-fi. Join security chief, Renfield Briggs and the beautiful, Arizona Dos Santos on a mind bending journey. The two are on the trail of a legendary belt of power. But so are a lot of other people...no problem, Arizona has a plan.
name: The Polysonic Blues

volume.name: Afterburner: Tales of the Cool and the Wicked

description: Albert the Alien is the first foreign exchange student from another planet! His adventures during his first week on Earth include battling a Mecha-Alien School Supply Monster, saving the cafeteria from his hungry alien lunch, and solving the mystery of the Locker Theif! Collects Chapters 1-8 of the Harvey Award nominated adventure series.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Albert the Alien: New In School

description: Set in both our world, and an alternate world called The Ring, ASYLUM Volume 1: New Born, collects issues 1-4 into a trade paperback that is the beginning of the Asylum saga! Glass Asylum cares for people with all manner of mental health issues, but in the alternate world of "The Ring", the patients are called Divine Childen. They have special gifts corresponding to their psychosis, and are part of an oppressive army, led by the mysterious diety, Father. Revered like angels by some and hated like demons by others, Father's Divine Family has dwindled in numbers and lost its grasp on the Castoffs they rule over. In this first volume of Asylum, Divine Children begin appearing in The Ring and are recruited into Father's Family as a holy army to regain power. But as new Children are brought into the fold, they question Father's power and methods and begin to wonder if they want to be part of the privileged and elite Divine Family.
name: Volume 1

description:
In the future, super computers and servers the size of buildings, push the information age into an era of growth unlike any other historical age. World governments create laws mandating collective gathering and sharing of all data both past and present. In order to control information companies and governments hide data using advanced technologies and COLD WAR tactics

Special agencies and secret organizations form groups or special teams called HARVESTERS. These special teams use tech, weapons and unconventional strategies to discover the secrets powerful institutions kill to protect.

This is the story of one team of HARVESTERS, tasked to meet and extract an informant scientist with valuable company intelligence. When the scientist doesn't make the rendezvous, the team must find him and the retrieve the special data he was carrying. Operations never go as planned, especially when genetically modified tigers are involved.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Back In The Papers

Martin Cooney departs from his hometown in Ireland where a lifetime of adventure awaits. He soon finds himself on patrol in Cleveland, where he is investigating his first murder, and encounters a deadly gang known as "The Trio".
name: Back In The Papers

description:
The Road to Hell

The year is 2053; the World is at War. The United States leads a massive military campaign in the Middle East. Captain John Dante is soldier in the United States Army Special Forces; while his squad of elite soldiers are on a mission to retrieve a weapon of great power, Dante finds himself trapped in a hellish nightmare.

Believing himself to be dead and hunted by demons, Dante, with the help of his deceased friend Virgil, must journey through the nine levels of Hell in search of Lucifer, who plans to bring about the apocalypse and unleash Hell on Earth by sacrificing the soul of Dante's love, Beatrice.
name: The Road to Hell

description: A horror sequel to L. Frank Baum's The Wonderful Wizard of Oz. Journey with Dorothy through a much darker vision of Oz.
"Precipitation." Artificial intelligence, a gun, ballet and a man from the Patent Office.
name: Part One

description:
One year after failure! One year after defeat! Join the Flare and his Fancymen as they set off to eliminate the evil organization Redux, who have sworn to wipe meta-humans off of the face of the Earth!

One year ago, Redux's leader, Prime, faced off against the Flare and the Dodger, the world's greatest heroes and founders of The Union - the world's first superhero team! But The Union failed, and Prime set off a bomb that leveled the entire city of New York!

Now, with both Prime and the Dodger gone, the Flare is determined to find the remaining members of Redux and bring them to justice!

End of WW2 special

The fourth issue of FKT, commemorating the 70th anniversary of the end of WW2
name: End of WW2 Special

description:
Jhaakob Comes to Earth

This origin story tells how Jhaakob arrives on our world, and how he first meets Rosie and Ben. It also provides an overview of the British immigration and asylum system, and tells new residents where they can go for more help.
name: Jhaakob Comes to Earth

description: Humanity's origins are not what we believed...

A black satirical comedy if only it wasn’t true. In the sweltering summer of 1963, at the height of Cold War paranoia, CIA agent Robert “Bob” Maheu is sent to Cuba on a suicide mission aptly titled Operation Good Times: to humiliate Fidel Castro during a live television broadcast by dosing the dictator with LSD and making his beard fall out. But Bob bears the permanent scars of the MKULTRA program, a dark secret in the untold history of the United States’ clandestine services. Overseeing Bob's mission back home is Dr. Gottlieb, the mad mastermind behind the Mk-Ultra program which tried to turn Americans like Bob into remote-controlled killing machines. But as the devious doctor discovers, Bob's humanity and his red-white-&-blue birthright to freedom and individuality remain just beneath the surface of his sock-puppet skin. This is the (mostly) true story of how one agency’s epic failure set the United States on a collision course with paranoia and peace. Collects issues 1-4.
name: GN

description:
Genesis

Kazuhiro Takano lost his desire to live after an unfortunate turn of events that scarred his life forever, but destiny had a plan for him. He got the chance to experience death in its pure manifestation and comes back from it to set things right. With the aid of an ancient medallion, "Kazu" is given a new life with a marked purpose. He was granted an opportunity to eliminate a primordial threat, reborn with a dark agenda against human kind and its place in the universe. "Kazu" must destroy the menace responsible of changing his life in ways he could have never imagined. He was made an immortal God among men, mortal among his new kind.
name: Genesis

description:
13 year old Aisling is sent to a strict summer school on a remote island by her parents. But Aisling soon discovers that the school is not what it seems...

LORD is a horror/drama set in 1970's Ireland that explores the evil that lurks in a closed community.

**TRIGGER WARNING : Depictions of abuse and violence.
name: GN

description:
The noise of thunder, part one

Tessa Theus was a heroine. Still is, but she doesn't remember much since Saturn, the ruler of Manifest, defeated her two years ago. With the help of a former ally, the mysterious Spectral Wayfarer, Tessa tries to regain her memory and her powers. Meanwhile, a conspiracy against Saturn is in motion...
name: The Noise of Thunder, Part One

description:
Hot August Night Part 1

The day the monsters came the world was changed forever. Cities were destroyed. Nations crumbled. But from the wreckage one man rose to stand against them. To give his daughter a better future, he fights the monsters - Monster Matador!

Witness the origin of the Monster Matador in Hot August Night Part 1
name: Hot August Night Part 1

description:
The Man With No Name

On a faraway planet, a stranger with no memories, no destination, and no name sets out on a bizarre quest. He is... nameless.
name: The Man With No Name

description:
Dragons And Flowers

Hundreds of Dragons attack a City. A boy is given a message by a goddess; and the fate of Arofa, the continent above the clouds, shall be change forever. Come and travel with Astor Adima a young noble with a restless spirit, and discover the mysteries that surround this new, and yet familiar world.
name: Dragons And Flowers

description:
Episode 1

Here is episode #1 in the graphic novel adaptation of the #1 Bestselling epic fantasy novel A QUEST OF HEROES, with over 900 five star reviews!

From #1 Bestselling author Morgan Rice comes the debut of a dazzling new fantasy series. A QUEST OF HEROES (BOOK #1 IN THE SORCERER'S RING) revolves around the epic coming of age story of one special boy, a 14 year old from a small village on the outskirts of the Kingdom of the Ring. The youngest of four, the least favorite of his father, hated by his brothers, Thorgrin senses he is different from the others. He dreams of becoming a great warrior, of joining the King's men and protecting the Ring from the hordes of creatures on the other side of the Canyon. When he comes of age and is forbidden by his father to try out for the King's Legion, he refuses to take no for an answer: he journeys out on his own, determined to force his way into King's Court and be taken seriously.

With its sophisticated world-building and characterization, A QUEST OF HEROES is an epic tale of friends and lovers, of rivals and suitors, of knights and dragons, of intrigues and political machinations, of coming of age, of broken hearts, of deception, ambition and betrayal. It is a tale of honor and courage, of fate and destiny, of sorcery. It is a fantasy that brings us into a world we will never forget, and which will appeal to all ages and genders.
name: Episode 1

volume.name: A Quest of Heroes: The Graphic Novel

description:
Luiza Brillante is a big city girl who loves to people watch! With so many people and places to see, there are always new adventures to find, and every once in a while, she gets to help someone out too! While the problems don't go away, they learn that together, they can find an easier way to deal with them! Walk around with Luiza and see how she always finds a reason to smile!!

"A Reason to Smile!" is a children's book about a little kid who is a walking silver lining and is inspired by the art style of comic book's and animation. This is the first volume collecting some of Luiza's experiences in the city she calls home.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Hands of Red

A band of disgruntled knights are hired to steal from the King. The heist runs the gamut of death, destruction, and desire, with a return on treasures of unknown power. But betrayal brings distrust, and loyalty is stretched to the limit in this exciting tale of skill, greed, and thievery.
name: Hands of Red

description: An Amish family feud escalates into a battle of giant-sized, wooden robots! The world's first entry into the exciting AMISHPUNK genre!
Two bone-chilling short stories, by Kyle James Smith & Gabe Sapienza.

Eighteen Lives

When a villainous team known as The Elite steal the DaVinci Codex, the daring duo known as Siamese must bring them to justice.
name: Eighteen Lives

description:
Chapter One: And Hell Followed With Him

A psychological horror tale about a random act of violence that builds to a crescendo of unhinged brutality and eventually brings the criminals face-to-face with the result of their monstrous act.
name: Chapter One: And Hell Followed With Him

description:
LOG#ONE

Space, a place where dreams reach out across an endless ocean of stars. It is here, that destiny is fortified and the simple hero...becomes legend. The greatest life experience that can be summoned from the ashes of a fallen empire...is that nothing last forever. But, what happens to the children that are to inherit rule over billions? Do they become forgotten in time and fade into memory just as their home...or do they fight to be remembered? This is the story of one such orphan, the prince-king to one of the greatest dynasties in the universe...his name, Joshua Fallscar.

In the tradition of classics such as Trigun, Kenshin, Outlaw Star, Slayers, Cowboy Bebop...and many more, comes the next big space manga, SPACE POP!

36+ Pages of Space Action!

Space Opera/ Action-Adventure/ Fantasy/ Comedy

Bonus Content: the "Slice of Life" short CHIBIPOP! #1 with Art by: Amon Salgado!
name: LOG#ONE

description:
This book is a compilation of the outlandish experiences of a public high school teacher. Most of these poignant stories are humorous, some are tragic.

The author's hope is that, by telling these honest tales, congress will realize the important role teachers play and pay them, like, a bazillion more dollars.
name: True Stories From A Classroom

description: When an artificial intelligence prototype is stolen from a top technology corporation, Oversight is brought in to apprehend it. Meanwhile, Beta has growing pains working with a new partner.
name: Chapter One

description:
They dug too deep.

They couldn't be told.

A group of archaeologists searching for signs of a lost civilization deep in a long extinct volcano discover that the answers may just lead to their undoing. Some things buried were buried for a reason. Some things once unearthed cannot be undone...

A tense and terrifying one-shot from writer and colourist John-Paul Bove (Teenage Mutant Turtles, Transformers, Judge Dredd) and artist Conor Boyle (Cross), featuring a cover painted by Ben Oliver (Marvel and DC comics).

In this issue, Earl, Steve, and Chupie head to the pacific northwest for a little getaway to Steve's parents house. But before Chupie can even bite into his delicious moose leg, the boys are dispatched even further north for a disturbance in Alaska, near the mysterious Selawik Lake.

The Marlowe Gallery

In Vincent's hands, murder is an art form. In this suspenseful send up of the art world, a charming but deadly painter named Vincent paints the town red using blood as his medium of choice. Vincent has made a name for himself in the art world by creating paintings out of his victims without ever getting caught. When an obsessed art collector gets too close to his secret Vincent plots to make the greedy collector history- art history.
name: The Marlowe Gallery

description: A bold adaptation of H. P. Lovecraft's only science fiction story. Experience a deep, welling horror on an alien planet; something that means everything is gone forever, even though it's right in front of your face. The light fog of your gasping breath makes it disappear, bit by hopeless bit.

Responsible for the violent death of a young girl, Isaac is banished to the savage world of the Wasteland, along with his mother and brother. Desperate to reinstate his family to Legion, Isaac aligns himself with the Helm Clan - a family of bounty hunters - to seek a replacement child.

Betrayed during a raid on a village, he flees with a girl, hoping to reach his family before the Clan can track him down. But Rose, his prize, is not what Isaac expects, and Legion may not be the place for him after all.
name: Exile

description: "Where Do We Go From Here?" is a story of the past and the future and the people that make us who we are. Also, there is a cat.

volume.name: Where Do We Go From Here?

description:
Between the end of the 80's and the beginning of the 90's, a small apartment in the North Zone of Sao Paulo shook with the chatter, screams, the tinkling of glasses and bottles and the boombox at its highest volume.

Mixed with the sound of guitars, drums and bass, words had to be guessed amongst sips and puffs from smoking mouths.

There were new packs of cigarettes, alcohol and records constantly being added into the combustion that burned throughout the night.

And it all happened again by the end of every week.

A few came back and brought friends who brought other friends, and some came back the next month.

Some took a long while to come back and some didn't come back at all.

Until one day, no one returned.

I didn't either.

But I still remember a lot of things and talked to a lot of people.

Now, everything I know about some of them is in this book.

My 80's memory lane.
